text: Lycée Frédéric Mistral is a sixth-form college/senior high school in Fresnes, Val-de-Marne, France, in the Paris metropolitan area. there are about 1,000 general high school students and 500 vocational high school students with a combined total of fewer than 1,500 students."Histoire du lycée." Lycée Frédéric Mistral. Retrieved on September 7, 2016. it had about 1,600 students. In 2016 Le Parisien described the school as "prestigious". "Des parents d'élèves [...] dans la section professionnelle du prestigieux lycée." As of 2011 it was ranked as the no. 1 senior high/sixth-form in the . Its Baccalaureate pass rate in 2010 was 96.1%. ==History== Lycée intercommunal de Fresnes opened in 1973 with about 360 students. It was later renamed after Mistral. In 2016 teachers went on strike and parents of students blocked the school entrance to protest against issues in the professional education section. ==References== ==External links== * Lycée Frédéric Mistral Category:Lycées in Val-de-Marne
